abstract: Mr. Gillum, the Democratic nominee for governor, supports higher corporate taxes and Medicare for all. He also has a lobbyist as a top adviser and, as mayor of Tallahassee, was on the payroll of a consultant.
snippet: Mr. Gillum, the Democratic nominee for governor, supports higher corporate taxes and Medicare for all. He also has a lobbyist as a top adviser and, as mayor of Tallahassee, was on the payroll of a consultant.
lead_paragraph: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. — City Hall never did seem big enough for Andrew Gillum.

abstract: Grimy, daring and deadly, dirt-track racing has become a magnet for fans — and a threat to the Nascar status quo.
snippet: Grimy, daring and deadly, dirt-track racing has become a magnet for fans — and a threat to the Nascar status quo.
lead_paragraph: The air was heavy with exhaust and motor oil at Charlotte Motor Speedway in North Carolina as I waited for Tony Stewart to arrive. Charlotte was hosting the 2017 championship weekend for the World of Outlaws, the premier dirt-racing series in the country, and all 60,000 tickets had sold out well in advance. Stewart, the ex-Nascar star, was late — running on “Tony time,” a handler told me — so I went for a walk along the dusty pit road to look at the scores of racecars lined up. “You’ll probably have to run at some point,” I was warned. “And remember: The cars can’t turn right.” Their larger right-side tires help them around a loop that only bends left and, indeed, make it nearly impossible to turn right.

abstract: The dynamic star is trying to keep comedy alive at a moment when Hollywood — and its audience — can’t seem to crack a smile.
snippet: The dynamic star is trying to keep comedy alive at a moment when Hollywood — and its audience — can’t seem to crack a smile.
lead_paragraph: Melissa McCarthy was hovering six feet above Los Angeles, in a glass tube, wearing a helmet and goggles. Her limbs were spread out like a starfish, with her legs bent at the knee as if she were a teenager reading on her stomach on her bed and her arms bent at the elbow so that had she been upright, they would have made the shape of a cactus.

headline_main: On Politics With Lisa Lerer: Doing What She Can

abstract: Two years ago, the Columbus band unexpectedly broke out big with the anxiety anthems of “Blurryface.” Can they keep doing things their own way in the face of mass success?
snippet: Two years ago, the Columbus band unexpectedly broke out big with the anxiety anthems of “Blurryface.” Can they keep doing things their own way in the face of mass success?
lead_paragraph: COLUMBUS, OHIO — The word “unlikely” pops up so often when discussing the duo Twenty One Pilots, it should come as no surprise that the band’s early strategy for building itself into a local touring machine was not inviting fans to 99 percent of its shows.

abstract: Democrats are largely ducking the topic on the campaign trail, but few people in Washington doubt that it will be on the table if they win the House.

lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — President Trump was energized. Fresh from the fight to confirm Brett Kavanaugh, he was firing up thousands of supporters at a rally by complaining about how Democrats had treated his nominee and how they may yet try to remove Justice Kavanaugh from the bench.

abstract: The Las Vegas couple, who had already given $55 million, delivered a last-minute infusion of cash to help the party remain in control in Washington.
snippet: The Las Vegas couple, who had already given $55 million, delivered a last-minute infusion of cash to help the party remain in control in Washington.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Sheldon and Miriam Adelson, the Las Vegas Republicans who have already spent more money on federal races this year than any other donors in either political party, are piling even more of their casino fortune into Republicans’ campaign efforts, people with knowledge of their plans said Thursday.

headline_main: Adelsons Give at Least $25 Million More to G.O.P. for Midterms
headline_print_headline: Adelsons Add $25 Million To Republican War Chest

abstract: Party leaders are building a firewall around a few dozen purple districts, and cutting off lawmakers who appear unable to win.
snippet: Party leaders are building a firewall around a few dozen purple districts, and cutting off lawmakers who appear unable to win.
lead_paragraph: DALLAS — Vice President Mike Pence laid out a hopeful vision for the midterm elections this week as he campaigned for Representative Pete Sessions of Texas, telling Republican donors that candidates like Mr. Sessions could stop Democrats from winning the House in November.

abstract: California faces concerns about its economic stability and a possible recession just as Gov. Jerry Brown heads out the door.
snippet: California faces concerns about its economic stability and a possible recession just as Gov. Jerry Brown heads out the door.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — It has the highest concentration of billionaires in the country. It exports more  computers than any other state. It is the nation’s largest producer of agriculture products by far: More than $6 billion in dairy products alone last year.
